data.title: Agriculture biotechnology market to reach $144.25B by 2030, growing at 9.4% CAGR from $92.19B in 2025 -Report.
data.description: A recent report from MarketsandMarkets™ reveals that the agriculture biotechnology market is expected to see significant growth in the coming years. Starting at USD 92.19 billion in 2025, it is projected to reach USD 144.25 billion by 2030, with a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 9.4%. This market is experiencing rapid expansion globally, showcasing the increasing importance and adoption of biotechnology in the agricultural sector.

data.title: Lear Corp (NYSE: LEA) reported Q3 2025 revenue of $5.7 billion, a significant achievement in automotive technology sector.
data.description: Headquartered in Southfield, Michigan, Lear Corporation (NYSE: LEA), a prominent figure in automotive technology focused on Seating and E-Systems, announced its financial results for the third quarter of 2025. One of the key highlights during this period was achieving a revenue of $5.7 billion.

data.title: OneMain Holdings reports impressive 3Q 2025 results - Diluted EPS $1.67, C&I adjusted diluted EPS $1.90, managed receivables $25.9B. Dividend raised by 1% to $1.05/share and approved $1.0B share repurchase program.
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, the Diluted Earnings Per Share (EPS) was reported at $1.67, while the Commercial and Industrial (C&I) adjusted Diluted EPS stood at $1.90. Managed receivables for the same period amounted to $25.9 billion. Additionally, there was a 1% increase in the quarterly dividend, which now stands at $1.05 per share. The Board of Directors has also sanctioned a $1.0 billion share repurchase initiative. This information was disclosed out of New York on October 31, 2025.

data.title: Chevron Q3 2025 earnings: $3.5B ($1.82/share), down from $4.5B ($2.48/share) in Q3 2024. Hess acquisition costs and forex impact noted.
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, Chevron Corporation (NYSE: CVX) announced earnings of $3.5 billion, equivalent to $1.82 per share on a diluted basis. This is a decrease from the third quarter of 2024 when earnings were reported at $4.5 billion, or $2.48 per diluted share. The earnings for the current quarter were impacted by a net loss of $235 million, attributed to severance and transaction costs due to the acquisition of Hess Corporation (Hess). However, this was partly offset by the fair value measurement of Hess shares. Foreign currency fluctuations also played a role, contributing to an increase in earnings by $147 million.

data.title: Emerald Holding reported Q3 2025 revenue of $330.7 million, a $38.7 million increase (+13.3%) from the prior year period.
data.description: Emerald Holding, Inc. (NYSE: EEX), the leading producer of trade shows and related events in the U.S., announced its third-quarter financial results for the period ending September 30, 2025. In the year-to-date 2025 financial highlights, the company recorded revenues totaling $330.7 million. This marked a $38.7 million increase, up by 13.3% from the same period in the previous year. The growth was mainly attributed to revenues generated from acquisitions and increased Organic Revenues. Organic Revenues also saw significant growth during this period.

data.title: Skyscanner predicts 2026 travel trends like Glowmads, Shelf Discovery, Bookbound — 7 trends shaping future travel.
data.description: Skyscanner, a prominent travel app, has unveiled its Travel Trends Report for 2026 highlighting seven key trends that are expected to shape the travel industry in the upcoming year. The trends, including Glowmads, Shelf Discovery, Altitude Shift, Bookbound, Catching Flights and Feelings, Family Miles, and Destination Check-in, offer unique insights into the changing travel behaviors of individuals. This report was launched in London on October 31, 2025. With the travel industry constantly evolving, these trends provide valuable information for industry professionals and travelers alike as they navigate the ever-changing landscape of travel.

data.title: Kuick Research's study on US Orphan Drug Market forecasts $190 billion opportunity by 2030 with 850 drugs in trials.
data.description: Kuick Research has released a study on the US Orphan Drug Market, providing insights for investors and stakeholders. The report covers financial, regulatory, and scientific aspects, offering data on designated orphan products, pricing, and clinical pipelines. The market is projected to exceed US$190 billion by 2030, with over 850 orphan drugs in clinical trials and 500 already marketed. Information on pricing, dosage, and sales of over 400 orphan drugs is included, with more than 150 drugs represented in charts and tables. The report is available on Benzinga.com for a detailed analysis of the rare disease therapeutics domain.
